<TITLE> Nation remembers independence martyrs </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 26 (bdnews24.com)The nation Wednesday remembered Liberation War martyrs with prayers, wreaths and emotion-charged functions on Independence and National Day. The day was heralded with the offerings of wreaths by President Iajuddin Ahmed and chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed at the National Memorial in Savar. Later, a human sea including leaders and workers of different political parties and sociocultural organisations thronged the mausoleum. In the districts outside the capital, the day was observed with similar enthusiasm. Different parties and organisations arranged discussion meetings and cultural functions to mark the occasion. bdnews24.com Savar correspondent Selim Ahmed reports: Thousands of people thronged the National Memorial in Savar. The president, the chief adviser, house speaker, the deputy speaker, cabinet members, chiefs of the three forces and workers of different political parties and socio-cultural organisations laid wreaths at the memorial in a show of respect to the martyrs. Fakhruddin reached the National Memorial around 5.45am. Iajuddin reached there at 5.57am. The president was the first to lay a wreath at the mausoleum, followed by the chief adviser. They signed the visitors' book. Awami League leaders and workers led by party presidium member Tofail Ahmed laid wreaths at the mausoleum around 7.30am. Party central leaders including Amir Hossain Amu, Abdur Razzak, Suranjit Sengupta, Syed Ashraful Islam, advocate Shahara Khatun and Saber Hossin Chowdhury were present. The pro-reform BNP leaders and workers led by retired major Hafizuddin Ahmed offered flowers at the mausoleum around 8pm. Pro-Khaleda BNP leaders and workers led by retired brigadier general ASM Hannan Shah offered flowers at 9.20am. Jatiya Party leaders barrister Anisul Islam Mahmud, Ruhul Amin Hawlader and others laid flowers at the mausoleum. Next came Progotishil Ganotantrik Party (PDP) leader Ferdaus Ahmad Quarishi and LDP leader retired Col Oli Ahmed. Besides flowers were also offered on behalf of Dhaka University, Jahangirnagar University, Bangladesh Open University, Sher-e-Bangla Agriculture University, Jagannath University and BUET. The administrations and common people took up different programmes to observe Independence and National Day. bdnews24.com
